Lying in a Beijing military hospital
in 1990, General Wang Zhen told a visitor he felt betrayed.
Decades after he risked his life fighting for an egalitarian
utopia, the ideals he held as one of Communist China’s founding
fathers were being undermined by the capitalist ways of his
children -- business leaders in finance, aviation and computers.  To contact the editor responsible for this slideshow:
